Our First Rmd

M119 Section 1

2024-09-20

Given a function \(f(x)=x^2\) and funtion \(h(x) = f(x+2)\), we want to calculate the input for \(h(x)\) when the output is 4. Some things to notice about this calculation is that taking the square root of a squared quantity gives an absolute value, this leads to two inputs that are connected to the output 4 for the function \(h\).
